        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 17 at 2:56AM CDT until August 17 at 3:15AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 256 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near South Shore to South Deering to near Roseland to
Crestwood, moving southeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Chicago Lawn, Englewood, Oak Lawn, Merrionette Park, Summit, Oakbrook
Terrace, Stickney, Westmont, Avalon Park, Grand Boulevard, South
Deering, Hyde Park, South Chicago, Hodgkins, South Shore, Roseland,
Woodlawn, Armour Square, Fuller Park, Forest View, Douglas, Burnham,
Hickory Hills, Justice, and Clarendon Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
